This paper deals with geometric matching problems involving disks, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the problem involves finding a perfect matching, which is a classic topic in combinatorics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the weight of the matching, which suggests that it may be related to optimization and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper may be relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.SI) as it involves finding a solution to a geometric problem.
